t0.c: Simple example for thread usage
t01.c: Shows how to pass a struct as argument to thread function.
t1.c: Demonstrates two threads run in parallel using gettimeofday
parallel.c: Run 'cnt' number of threads in parallel. cnt is a command line 
			argument. Argument (&i) passed to thread function is shared. 
			This can create problem in thread function
thcount.c: Demonstrates the maximum number of thread that can be created. 
			Also, shows how to pass arguments to a thread function.
tret.c: Shows how to return value to the parent thread.
t2.c: Shows the problem due to two threads updating a shared variable
t2mutex.c: Use of lock to use a shared variable exclusively
